      • setLink

        public void setLink(ILink link,
                    IConnectionPoint connectionPoint,
                    Class<?> processorClass,
                    boolean listenGroup)
        Description copied from interface: IFIXMessageProcessor
        Adds given ILink object to end of message processor chains for handling messages for given connection point.

        The listenGroup parameter is only used if the link is directed. In that case, it indicates whether the this message processor is in the chain that the link listens to or routes to.

        Specified by:
        setLink in interface IFIXMessageProcessor
        Parameters:
        link - Link to be added to end of message processor chain.
        connectionPoint - Connection point of chain we are adding to.
        processorClass - Class of chain. This will be IFIXSource for the source processing chain or IFIXListener for listener processing chain.
        listenGroup - true if the link is directed and we are adding the listener portion of the link. In other words, we are looking for the last in a chain of listeners.

      • setStoresMessages

        public void setStoresMessages(boolean storesMessages)
        Description copied from interface: IFIXMessageProcessor
        Specify whether this message processor stores references to the message objects it processes.

        The default, to be safe, is true. However, if your message processor knows that it never keeps references to messages, it may be useful to indicate that fact because it can enable Catalys to reuse message objects, leading to increased performance.

        Note however that for messages to be reused all message processors in a session's pipeline would have to not store message references.

        A good time to call this method is in openComponent(), which you can override if you are extending FIXMessageProcessorBase.

        Specified by:
        setStoresMessages in interface IFIXMessageProcessor
        Parameters:
        storesMessages - True if this message processor can store references to processed messages.
        See Also:
        IFIXMessageProcessor.isStoresMessages()

      • setSynchronizedNotifications

        protected final void setSynchronizedNotifications(boolean value)
        The same instance of a message processor can be in the source and listener chains of multiple FIX sessions. This method specifies whether message events should be forwarded to other message processors in the chain in a synchronized fashion (ie by only one session/thread at a time), or whether concurrent forwards are possible.

        Per default notifications are synchronized.

        You can call this from subclasses to override the default value. However notice that the value will only be taken into account during openComponent() and refreshComponent().

        Parameters:
        value - whether notifications should be synchronized

      • isSynchronizedNotifications

        public final boolean isSynchronizedNotifications()
        The same instance of a message processor can be in the source and listener chains of multiple FIX sessions. This method indicates whether message events are forwarded to other message processors in a synchronized fashion (ie by only one session/thread at a time).
        Returns:
        the currently active synchronizeNotifications value
        See Also:
        setSynchronizedNotifications(boolean)

      • addMessageHistory

        protected void addMessageHistory(IMessage mess)
        Common code for adding message history to a message if it is supported.

        This default implementation adds a reference to this object to the message history (ie history.add( this )).

        Parameters:
        mess - Message to add history to.
